SIMPLE: western
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Western
<hw>West"ern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the west; situated in the west,
or in the region nearly in the direction of west; being in that quarter
where the sun sets; <as>as, the <ex>western</ex> shore of France; the
<ex>western</ex> ocean</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Far o'er the glowing <qex>western</qex> main.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Moving toward the west; <as>as, a ship makes a
<ex>western</ex> course</as>; coming from the west; <as>as, a
<ex>western</ex> breeze</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Western Church</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Latin
Church</cref>, under <er>Latin</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Western
empire</b></col> <fld>(Hist.)</fld>, <cd>the western portion of the
Roman empire, as divided, by the will of Theodosius the Great, between
his sons Honorius and Arcadius, <sc>a. d.</sc> 395.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Westerner</ent>⟦br⟧
